               <p>JOHN COOPER. I am a <rs id="t18270913-181-viclabel1026" type="occupation">sawyer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-181-victim1738 t18270913-181-viclabel1026"></join>. I was at work for Mr. Meggs, in <placeName id="t18270913-181-crimeloc1027">Kingsland-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-181-crimeloc1027" type="placeName" value="Kingsland-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-181-crimeloc1027" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-181-off1024 t18270913-181-crimeloc1027"></join>. I left three saws and a line, in the saw-pit house where I was at work, about six o'clock, on the 16th or 17th of August; I fastened the door after me, and when I returned the next morning, the place had<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182709130102"></xptr>been broken open, and the tools were gone - the saws were found at a saw-maker's, in Whitechapel, a day or two afterwards.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-181-person1740">
                  JOHN 
                  FOALE
               <interp inst="t18270913-181-person1740" type="surname" value="FOALE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-181-person1740" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-181-person1740" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I work for Mr. Hughes, a saw-maker, of Church-lane, Whitechapel. I bought these saws of the prisoner, as old steel; they weighed 171/2lbs. I gave him 11/2d. a lb. for them. I did not ask him whether they were his - I considered them as old saws - and, being worn out, I bought them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-181-person1741">
